Works perfectly. Here's the full program:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

Console.WriteLine(JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options));

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

`JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` is new in .NET 11 — it joins the existing `CamelCase`, `SnakeCaseLower/Upper`, and `KebabCaseLower/Upper` policies. It converts the record's lowercase positional-parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) in the JSON output with no custom code needed.
